The stock market index rose from 600 or so in 1985 to more than 12,000 by 1990 .
Meanwhile , the price of property rose from an average of NT$ 71,800 per ping -LRB- about 3.3 square meters -RRB- in 1986 to NT$ 284,500 per ping in <COREF ID="24" TYPE="IDENT">1989</COREF> .
At <COREF ID="24" TYPE="IDENT">that time</COREF> , great opportunities for making money stared one right in the face .
